  "prompt": "How do I tell a girl if I am not interested?",
  "response": "Here are some respectful ways to tell a girl you're not interested:\n\n1. Be direct but kind\n- Be clear and honest\n- Use a gentle tone\n- Avoid being harsh or mean\n\n2. Examples of what to say:\n- \"I appreciate your interest, but I don't feel a romantic connection\"\n- \"You're great, but I don't see us as more than friends\"\n- \"I don't think we're a good match\"\n\n3. Communication tips:\n- Do it in person if possible\n- Be sincere\n- Don't give false hope\n- Keep it brief\n- Show respect\n\n4. What to avoid:\n- Making up excuses\n- Being rude\n- Ghosting\n- Giving mixed signals\n- Being overly apologetic\n\n5. After telling her:\n- Give her space\n- Be consistent with your message\n- Maintain politeness\n\n6. If it's in a friendship context:\n- Emphasize that you value her friendship\n- Make it clear you want to remain friends\n- Be gentle but firm\n\nRemember, honesty and kindness are key when communicating your feelings.",
